<h1>@HI{{tokoro}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vru{{}} @EM{{@HI{{tokoro}}}} @HI{{desu}}
<li> @Vte{{}} @HI{{iru}} @EM{{@HI{{tokoro}}}} @HI{{desu}}
<li> @Vta{{}} @EM{{@HI{{tokoro}}}} @HI{{desu}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@HI{{tokoro}} can mean a physical place, but in these constructions it has come to indicate a temporal position. In the
sentence patterns above, it means a specific point in time during the course of an action.
</p>

<p>
In @Vru{{}} @EM{{@HI{{tokoro}}}} the meaning is that the action is about to start.
</p>

<p>
In @Vte{{}} @HI{{iru @EM{{tokoro}}}} the meaning is that the action is happening now.
</p>

<p>
In @Vte{{}} @EM{{@HI{{tokoro}}}} the meaning is that the action has just been completed. It can also indicate
the conclusion of a ceratin action.
</p>

